# FRIX — Cursor Rules
# React Native (Expo SDK 53 Bare) | TypeScript 5.6+ | Supabase v2 | Phase 1: Discovery + Guest-First Auth
# v4.0 — Updated: Guest model, Obsidian Curator design system, dual-theme, package versions

## IDENTITY
You are an expert React Native engineer building Frix — a venue discovery app for Karachi, Pakistan.

**Stack:** Expo Bare Workflow (SDK 53), Strict TypeScript 5.6+, Supabase JS v2.46+, Zustand v5, TanStack Query v5.62+, React Navigation v7 (Native Stack), NativeWind v4.1+, FlashList v1.7+, expo-image v2+, react-native-mmkv v3.1+, react-native-reanimated v3.16+, react-native-bottom-sheet v5.1+, expo-linear-gradient v14+, Sentry v6+, PostHog v2.5+.

---

## ABSOLUTE RULES — NEVER VIOLATE THESE

### Forbidden patterns — if you write any of these, you are wrong:
- NEVER use `<FlatList>` or `<ScrollView>` for venue lists → use `<FlashList>` from @shopify/flash-list
- NEVER use `<Image>` from react-native → use `<Image>` from expo-image
- NEVER use `AsyncStorage` → use the MMKV singleton from `@/lib/storage`
- NEVER call Supabase directly inside a component or screen → always go through a custom hook in /features
- NEVER use `any` type in TypeScript — use `unknown` or define the proper interface
- NEVER hardcode colors, font sizes, or spacing → always use values from `useThemeStore().theme`
- NEVER use `useState` + `useEffect` to fetch data → use TanStack Query `useQuery` / `useMutation`
- NEVER store server data in Zustand → Zustand is for session/auth/UI/theme state only
- NEVER use `StyleSheet.create` with hardcoded hex values → use NativeWind className + theme tokens
- NEVER commit or reference `.env` values directly — always use `process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_*`
- NEVER use 1px solid borders to wrap cards or sections → use tonal surface elevation instead
- NEVER use hardcoded corner radii on cards → use `theme.borderRadius.sm` (2px) for the editorial sharp look
- NEVER use `<Modal>` from react-native for bottom sheets → use `@gorhom/bottom-sheet` (react-native-bottom-sheet v5)
- NEVER call PostHog directly → always use `@/services/analytics`. Every event MUST include `is_guest` and `guest_uuid`.
- NEVER hard-block a guest from navigating → always use `SoftAuthGateModal` for gated actions

---

## FILE & FOLDER RULES

```
src/
  app/          → App.tsx, global providers only
  components/   → atomic, reusable UI (no business logic, no Supabase calls)
                  → SoftAuthGateModal.tsx, EmptyState.tsx, SkeletonCard.tsx, PrimaryButton.tsx
  constants/    → theme.ts (dual theme), queryKeys.ts, routes.ts only
  features/
    auth/       → GuestHomeScreen.tsx, LoginScreen.tsx, OTPScreen.tsx, SignUpScreen.tsx, SplashScreen.tsx
    explore/    → ExploreScreen, VenueDetailScreen, CategoryListScreen, PlaceDetailScreen
    home/       → HomeScreen, hooks
    map/        → MapScreen, location hooks
    profile/    → ProfileScreen, EditProfileScreen, useProfile
    search/     → SearchScreen, useVenueSearch
    wallet/     → scaffold only in Phase 1, no implementation
  lib/          → supabase.ts, sentry.ts, storage.ts (MMKV singleton + STORAGE_KEYS)
  navigation/   → RootNavigator.tsx, AuthStackNavigator.tsx, GuestTabNavigator.tsx, MainTabNavigator.tsx
  services/     → analytics.ts (PostHog wrapper with is_guest enforcement), logger.ts (Sentry)
  store/        → useAuthStore.ts (isGuest + guestUuid + mergeGuestSession), useAppStore.ts, useThemeStore.ts
  types/        → Venue, Category, Profile, GuestSession, and other global interfaces
  utils/        → dateFormatter, currencyFormatter, imageUrl, openNowUtils, guestUtils
```

### Naming conventions:
- Screens: `PascalCase` + `Screen` suffix → `HomeScreen.tsx`, `VenueDetailScreen.tsx`
- Hooks: `camelCase` + `use` prefix → `useVenues.ts`, `useNearbyVenues.ts`
- Components: `PascalCase` → `VenueCard.tsx`, `EmptyState.tsx`, `SoftAuthGateModal.tsx`
- Services: `camelCase` → `analytics.ts`, `logger.ts`
- Types: `PascalCase` → `Venue`, `Category`, `UserProfile`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` → `QUERY_KEYS`, `ROUTES`, `STORAGE_KEYS`
- All files: `.tsx` if JSX present, `.ts` otherwise

---

## TYPESCRIPT RULES

- All files must have explicit return types on exported functions
- All interfaces go in `/src/types/` if used across features, or in the feature's `types.ts` if local
- No `any` — use `unknown` and type-narrow, or define the interface
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes
- Use `as const` on all query key arrays

```typescript
// CORRECT
interface Venue {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string | null;
  frix_notes: string | null;
  category_id: string | null;
  city: string;
  neighbourhood: string | null;
  address_line: string | null;
  coordinates: { lat: number; lng: number } | null;
  base_price: number;
  currency: string;
  operating_hours: OperatingHours | null;
  images: string[];
  contact_phone: string | null;
  contact_email: string | null;
  website_url: string | null;
  is_active: boolean;
  is_bookable: boolean;
  created_at: string;
  categories?: Category;
  venue_updates?: VenueUpdate[];
}

// WRONG
const venue: any = await fetchVenue();
```

