## DESIGN SYSTEM RULES — THE OBSIDIAN CURATOR [NEW v4]

### Always use `useThemeStore` to get the current theme:
```tsx
import { useThemeStore } from '@/store/useThemeStore';

const MyComponent = () => {
  const { theme, isDarkMode } = useThemeStore();
  // Use theme.colors.*, theme.typography.*, theme.spacing.*
};
```

### Typography — Noto Serif for headlines, Manrope for body/UI:
```tsx
// CORRECT — headline (editorial)
<Text style={[theme.typography.headlineLarge, { color: theme.colors.onSurface }]}>
  Mohatta Palace
</Text>

// CORRECT — label (metadata, uppercase)
<Text style={[theme.typography.labelLarge, { color: theme.colors.onSurfaceVariant }]}>
  HISTORICAL · CLIFTON
</Text>

// WRONG — no hardcoded fonts or sizes
<Text style={{ fontSize: 24, fontWeight: '700', fontFamily: 'serif' }}>
```

### Surfaces — use tonal layering, NOT borders:
```tsx
// CORRECT — card sits on surfaceLow, card itself is surfaceHighest
<View style={{ backgroundColor: theme.colors.surfaceLow, padding: theme.spacing.md }}>
  <View style={{
    backgroundColor: theme.colors.surfaceHighest,
    borderRadius: theme.borderRadius.sm, // 2px — architectural sharpness
    ...theme.shadows.card,
  }}>
    {/* Card content */}
  </View>
</View>

// WRONG — never use this pattern
<View style={{ borderWidth: 1, borderColor: '#E5E7EB', borderRadius: 16 }}>
```

### Gold accents — use sparingly:
```tsx
// Gold is for: primary CTAs, active tab indicator, TONIGHT badge, Verified tick, Save icon (filled)
// NOT for: general text, card backgrounds, icons that don't represent action/status
backgroundColor: theme.colors.primary // gold in dark mode, deep blue in light mode
```

### Ghost border (used for floating elements only):
```tsx
// Top-left-only ghost border — catches light like edge of a physical object
borderTopWidth: 0.5,
borderLeftWidth: 0.5,
borderTopColor: theme.colors.outlineVariant,
borderLeftColor: theme.colors.outlineVariant,
```

### Glassmorphic surfaces (tab bar, bottom sheets):
```tsx
// Use expo-linear-gradient
import { LinearGradient } from 'expo-linear-gradient';

<LinearGradient
  colors={isDarkMode
    ? ['rgba(53,53,52,0.85)', 'rgba(28,27,27,0.95)']
    : ['rgba(255,255,255,0.9)', 'rgba(245,243,230,0.95)']
  }
  style={StyleSheet.absoluteFillObject}
/>
```

